      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): separate platform-incompatible skills from missing requirements",
        "body": "Fixes #89232\n\n## Summary\n\n`openclaw doctor` reported skills with a declared OS requirement that doesn't match the current platform (e.g. macOS-only `apple-notes`, `imsg`, `homebrew` on Linux/Windows) under the same \"Missing requirements\" count as genuinely-broken installs, and `doctor --fix` would prompt to disable them. Those skills aren't broken — they're inapplicable by design on this OS — and the noise hides real issues.\n\nThis derives a `platformIncompatible` flag from the **shared requirement evaluator's `missing.os`** (which already accounts for remote macOS node eligibility, not just local `process.platform`) and updates doctor so platform-mismatched skills are:\n- excluded from the \"Missing requirements\" count and surfaced as a single `Incompatible (platform mismatch, auto-skipped): N` line;\n- excluded from `doctor --fix`'s disable target, so it no longer prompts to disable inapplicable-but-not-broken skills.\n\n- `src/skills/discovery/status.ts` — expose `platformIncompatible` from the shared evaluator's `missing.os` (incl. remote macOS eligibility)\n- `src/commands/doctor-workspace-status.ts` — drop platform-incompatible from \"Missing requirements\", add single rollup line\n- `src/commands/doctor-skills-core.ts` — exclude platform-incompatible from `collectUnavailableAgentSkills` (the `doctor --fix` disable target)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** A skill whose declared OS requirement excludes this host (and that no remote node can satisfy) is no longer counted as a \"missing requirement\" nor offered for disable by `doctor --fix`; it is reported once under an \"Incompatible (platform mismatch)\" rollup, so genuinely-broken installs stay visible. Skills satisfiable via a remote macOS node are not flagged, because the flag follows the shared evaluator's `missing.os`.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Linux x86_64, Node.js v22, HEAD `455ff07c7bde7b4512055682ba468a03048f2535` based on `origin/main` `489efc8f5eb15066f007f820ea71398357ad08e8`. Production functions `buildWorkspaceSkillStatus` and `collectUnavailableAgentSkills` driven directly via `node --import tsx`, plus the Vitest suites.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```\nnode --import tsx -e 'Promise.all([import(\"./src/skills/discovery/status.ts\"), import(\"./src/skills/test-support/test-helpers.ts\"), import(\"./src/commands/doctor-skills-core.ts\")]).then(([m,h,d])=>{\n  const mk=(n,meta)=>({skill:h.createCanonicalFixtureSkill({name:n,description:\"t\",filePath:\"/tmp/\"+n,baseDir:\"/tmp\",source:\"test\"}),frontmatter:{},metadata:meta});\n  const r=m.buildWorkspaceSkillStatus(\"/tmp/ws\",{entries:[mk(\"mac-only\",{os:[\"darwin\"],requires:{}}),mk(\"portable\",{})]});\n  for(const s of r.skills) console.log(s.skillKey,\"platformIncompatible=\"+s.platformIncompatible);\n  console.log(\"collectUnavailable:\",JSON.stringify(d.collectUnavailableAgentSkills(r).map(s=>s.skillKey)));\n  console.log(\"Missing:\",r.skills.filter(s=>!s.eligible&&!s.disabled&&!s.blockedByAllowlist&&!s.platformIncompatible).length);\n})'\n\nOPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run \\\n  src/skills/discovery/status.test.ts \\\n  src/commands/doctor-workspace-status.test.ts \\\n  src/commands/doctor-skills.test.ts --reporter=dot\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n```\nplatform: linux\n  mac-only  platformIncompatible=true   (via missing.os)\n  portable  platformIncompatible=false  (via missing.os)\ncollectUnavailable (doctor --fix disable target): []   <- mac-only excluded\nMissing requirements: 0\n\nstatus.test.ts: 12 passed | doctor-workspace-status.test.ts: 6 passed | doctor-skills.test.ts: 9 passed\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The macOS-only skill on Linux resolves to `platformIncompatible=true` (via the shared evaluator's `missing.os`), drops out of both the doctor \"Missing requirements\" count (1 → 0) and the `doctor --fix` disable target (`collectUnavailableAgentSkills` → `[]`), and appears once under the \"Incompatible (platform mismatch)\" rollup. A portable skill stays `false`. `tsgo:core` passes.\n\n**What was not tested:** A live full `openclaw doctor` / `doctor --fix` run on Windows with the real ClawHub bundle (the reporter's environment), and an actual reachable remote macOS node; the platform-mismatch + remote-eligibility branch is exercised on Linux against macOS-only skills via the production status builder, the doctor disable collector, and the unit suites — the same code path.\n",
        "branch": "fix/89232-doctor-platform-skills",
